In view of the above noted deficiencies, we have recommended that:
Management identify the mode of procurement used in the hiring of the consultant;
The Municipal Accountant and Treasurer justify the payment of the transactions despite the lack of appropriation and absence of the BAC Resolution recommending the mode of procurement used and award of the contract;
The Municipal Mayor justify entering into contract without the concurrence of the majority of the BAC, lack of appropriation for the said purpose and absence of prior authorization from the Sangguniang Bayan;
Management clarify the terms of reference of all the contracts entered into by the LGU. Justify the increase in contract cost and extension of the contract; and
Management require the immediate submission of accomplishment reports by the hired consultants

In view of the above noted lapses, we have recommended the following:
Submit copy of the duly approved SWM Plan from the Solid Waste Management Commission;
Justify the noted lapses primarily the non-establishment of a sanitary landfill which will serve as the final disposal sites;
The MPDC sees to it that henceforth all relevant cost for the implementation of the SWMP is integrated to the Annual Budget as well as Annual Investment Plan. Coordination among the different offices is hereby advised;
The Municipal Mayor convenes the SWMB and seeks justification as to the reason for the low success rate for the implementation of SWM projects; and
The members of the SWMB revisit the provisions of the IRR of R.A. No. 9003. Henceforth, implement quality assurance/ monitoring mechanism to facilitate an efficient and effective implementation of the programs indicated in the SWMP.

In view of the foregoing observations, we have recommended that the following actions be undertaken:
The MDRRMO conduct the necessary VAA and formulate a LCCAP in accordance with Book 1 and 2 of the LCCAP Formulation to be integrated to the LDRRMP and AIP of the LGU;
Integrate the result of hazard mapping in the DRRM Plan of the LGU
The MDRRMO Designate/MSWDO or other personnel in-charge of the distribution of relief goods submit the required liquidation documents for audit purposes;
The Municipal Budget Officer exercise due diligence in the computation of the mandatory trust liabilities of the LGU;
The Municipal Accountant incorporates in the Notes to Financial Statements all required information pertaining to the LDRRM Fund;

